    <JimNotes><![CDATA[<p>You don&#39;t hear the term <em>torch song</em> so much anymore, and that&#39;s too bad. Love song is a rough equivalent, but that term is safe and sappy by comparison. If you&#39;re singing lyrics like &quot;I&#39;m going to love you, like nobody&#39;s love you, <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=MCj96k1A95g">come rain or come shine</a>,&quot; you&#39;re addressing someone you&#39;re &quot;carrying a torch for.&quot; Love songs imply sweetness and cuddling. Torch songs promise at least the possibility of furniture-busting sex.</p>]]></JimNotes>
    <JeffNotes><![CDATA[<p>Wordplay on &quot;torch songs&quot; today. Given my severe deficiencies in pop culture, I was thrilled to have recognized Jon Bon Jovi! But BLAZE OF GLORY? Maybe that was some witty reference to his &hellip; horse named Glory? BURNING LOVE ... maybe Elvis burned &hellip; Valentine&#39;s Day hearts? You know ... showing his disdain for the holiday?</p>

